I've rewritten this caption a dozen times because I want to make sure I properly convey just how over-the-moon excited and proud and terrified and HAPPY I am about this, but turns out it's hard to fit all of that in a few short paragraphs. So, short version: IT'S HAPPENING!! And I cannot wait to share SUCH A BAD INFLUENCE with you all. 

My deepest thanks to the absolutely incredible group of people who have ensured this book comes to life, especially @alexyarnold and the entire team at @quirkbooks and, of course, my wonderful agent @manadurphy ♥️

Stay tuned for more!!! And in the meantime, please know I appreciate your support of my writing/me more than you can ever know.

This was the key we were handed when we bought our house. Though we've updated the locks since, I didn't want to just throw the old key in a drawer. If you've followed me for a while, you know I love Framebridge. I've *always* wanted to try their object framing offering and this key felt like the perfect opportunity to do so. Luckily, @framebridge made the process easier than I could have ever imagined and I *love* the final result. I now plan on framing... basically everything??? #framebridge

#ad Creating a new schedule that makes me feel my best means making time for exercise. Ever since injuring myself while working out a couple years ago, I've known just how important stretching can be (both for staying healthy and healing) @gaiam 

For a long time, I felt like in order to stretch regularly, I had to LOVE traditional group yoga classes and/or be good at it, so I just ignored it all together. Now, just in time for National Yoga Month, I'm bringing my own solo, no-pressure, go-at-my-own-pace stretching and different forms of movement back into my life (hello, gardening!) and so far, it feels amazing. @gaiam 

PS: I'm wearing Gaiam's Seamless Everyday Tee here (my favorite workout/lounge top right now), though I do suggest opting for the *long-sleeve* version of the Seamless Everyday Tee if you're going to create a similar gardening/stretching routine... because, you know, poison ivy. #gaiam #ForEveryBody @kohls

In honor of @beccamfreeman's book coming out in less than one week, I treated myself to a beachside re-read, highlighting all the parts that made me laugh, feel, smile, or simply reminded me of Becca (this is obviously why the Chili's reference makes the first slide).

Those who know Becca know she works harder than anyone, and I know first hand that every step of this book was no exception. It's bursting with humor and wit and warmth and full of heart, from start to finish. I loved the line about the Popsicle (last slide), not only because the writing is so great but also because that's exactly how this book made me feel... warm and happy, in the best way. 

If you somehow haven't already, please join me in supporting Becca's hard work and incredible book by pre-ordering it RIGHT NOW! It makes more of a difference for an author's success than you can ever know. 📕 ♥️

#ad My favorite rug of ALL TIME is in what will one day be our dining room. We've held off having dinner parties in there, though, because more eating/drinking/hanging out with Winnie means, well, more messes, and I'm so scared of staining the rug. I'm a huge fan of @bissellclean products (we keep their handheld pet hair vacuum by our bed for refreshing our bedding daily), so when they sent me the brand new Little Green® HydroSteam® Pet portable deep cleaner, I knew I wanted to try it out! Before using it on our most beloved rug, I tried it out on another bright white rug we have (as well as some others in the house that I didn't film). The result? The most satisfying deep clean experience of my life. The mess? Gone. The process? Easy. The result? Clean rugs that looked and even *SMELLED* amazing. I truly can't wait to use this thing again as we finally use our dining room for actual dining and to know that our rug will be just fine, no matter what inevitable spills might occur! #BISSELL #DinnerParty

#ad Welcome to my morning routine, sponsored by @gaiam. I don't always do this routine perfectly (it took me an hour to get out of bed this morning), but the pillars of this routine are things that help me feel my best mentally, physically, and emotionally.  From reading to breakfast to exercise to writing, each task helps me feel my most peaceful and happy, and whenever I get too busy or overwhelmed, I simply start from zero and go back to this routine. #gaiam #ForEveryBody @kohls

So thrilled to share the cover for SUCH A BAD INFLUENCE *and* that @cosmopolitan shared an excerpt from the book along with the cover reveal (Is this real life????). You can pre-order SABI (or request from your local library! Or share with friends! Or mark as 'want to read' on Goodreads!) NOW! Perhaps have never been more excited to say LINK IN BIO in my life.

My deepest thanks to the entire @quirkbooks team (especially designer @lismadethis ) who made this gorgeous cover and SABI happen.

If you've supported me at any point in my career (online and IRL) you know who you are, and I love and appreciate you so much. Perhaps by June I'll find the exact right words to say thank you for helping a lifelong dream come true.

I can't wait for you all to read it. ☺️
